other_tests.findings: Mild-to-moderate amount of ascites noted in the perihepatic and perisplenic regions, focal dense material adjacent to a speck of air likely representing an appendicolith, a distended tubular structure measuring 14 mm likely representing a fluid-filled appendix, normal liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, and no free air or lymphadenopathy in the intra-abdominal cavity.
